Ad Text:
Lead SAP FI/CO Functional Analyst

Contract

Canberra

Excellent Federal Government Client

A SAP FI/CO (Financial Accounting / Controlling) Functional Consultant will play a critical role in managing Austrade’s financial processes and internal controlling. Austrade is looking for an SAP FI/CO Functional Consultant to join the Corporate Services Division.   

The FI/CO Functional Consultant will work closely with Corporate Systems and Finance Teams to deliver client-centred solutions. They will collaborate with the Chief Finance Officer, COO and GM Digital and Technology, and provide technical capability to create a more efficient and resilient instance of our SAP system (ECC6 on prem). 

Key duties and responsibilities

The SAP FI/CO Functional Consultant will be responsible for:  

Reviewing the existing core financial management functionality assessment and process to identify limitations and areas of improvement.  

Assessing current SAP system’s integration capabilities and customisations.  

Determine the modular functions within SAP that is currently utilised and recommend improvements that could be beneficial.  

Gathering input from finance team members and other stakeholders to understand their current problems, future needs and expectations to have a fit for purpose finance solution.   

Implementation and support of SAP Financials (focus on FICO Controlling – Cost Centre Accounting, Unsettled Costs, Month End Close, Overhead assessment, and settlement.)   

Design, customise, configure, and test various functions within FI/CO modules.  

Support End of Month and Year end closing processes and resolve issues.  

Setting up financial accounting and controlling processes.  

Engage with business stakeholders to understand their financial and controlling requirements, including identification of gaps, issues, and work around solutions.   

Identify opportunities for process improvement and optimisation of existing financial processes using SAP functionality, implementing best practice to enhance efficiency and effectiveness.  

Provide compliance and audit support to ensure that financial processes and configurations comply with relevant regulatory and accounting standards.   

Generate financial reports and financial data analytics to support business decision making.  

Maintain comprehensive documentation of configurations, customisations, and business processes.  

Triage and resolve SAP support queries in a timely manner i.e. provide support to end users, assisting with problem determination and resolution, and where possible, offering training.  

Act as a liaison between the finance functions and the technical team.   

Support capability uplift of the existing team, through mentoring and knowledge sharing to develop an effective systems governance function.  

Work self-directed and independently; may act as subject matter mentor to other business areas undertaking finance operations and activities.

Robert Half has partnered with a leading Australian organisation within the agricultural industrial / supply chain sector is seeking an experienced Business Analyst to take ownership of a critical portfolio of enterprise applications supporting large-scale operational and commercial activities.

Role Overview

We are seeking an experienced Senior Business Analyst with strong UKG Time & Attendance expertise to support the delivery, optimisation, and ongoing improvement of workforce management solutions.

You will act as a trusted advisor to the business, partnering closely with HR, Payroll, Workforce Planning, and Technology teams to ensure UKG solutions align with business objectives, compliance requirements, and operational needs.

This role requires someone who is comfortable working at both a strategic and hands-on level, from discovery and solution design through to implementation and benefits realisation.

Business Analysis & Discovery

Engage in end-to-end business analysis activities for UKG Time & Attendance initiatives
Plan and run discovery sessions to understand current-state processes, pain points, and future-state needs
Elicit, analyse, and validate business, functional, and non-functional requirements
Apply appropriate BA techniques including workshops, interviews, storyboarding, process modelling, and journey mapping

Requirements Definition & Management

Develop high-quality requirements artefacts including user stories, epics, use cases, process flows, business rules, and data definitions
Translate complex workforce management requirements (time capture, awards, overtime, leave, payroll interfaces) into clear, consumable documentation
Maintain requirements traceability from business objectives through to solution delivery
Support backlog creation, refinement, and prioritisation in collaboration with Product Owners and delivery teams

Stakeholder Engagement

Act as the primary point of contact for business analysis activities related to UKG Time & Attendance
Build strong relationships across HR, Payroll, Operations, and Technology teams
Facilitate requirement walkthroughs and design sessions to gain stakeholder alignment and sign-off
Communicate complex concepts clearly to both technical and non-technical audiences

You bring:

Proven experience working with UKG Time & Attendance (Kronos / UKG Dimensions / UKG Workforce Central)
Strong background in HR, Payroll, or Workforce Management systems
Experience working in complex, regulated environments with awards, EBAs, or industrial instruments
The ability to challenge requirements constructively and guide stakeholders toward the best outcome
Confidence working with ambiguity and making informed decisions
Excellent communication skills and the ability to translate between business and technical teams

Key Skills & Experience

5+ years' experience as a Business Analyst, with senior-level responsibility
Hands-on experience delivering UKG Time & Attendance solutions
Strong process modelling and requirements definition skills
Experience in Agile, Waterfall, or hybrid delivery environments
Exposure to integrations between UKG and payroll/HR systems
Ability to mentor and uplift BA capability within a team

Salary/Benefits:
$140,000 - $160,000 + Super

About the role:

Development and growth opportunities.

Davidson are proudly partnering with a large, complex organisation delivering multiple transformation initiatives to engage a Senior Change Analyst to support a Change Manager across two major programs of work.

This role suits a hands-on change professional who is comfortable operating in highly regulated, operationally critical environments and knows how to translate change strategy into real-world adoption.

The Opportunity

You'll support the delivery and embedding of change across two concurrent projects, working closely with project teams, sponsors, and impacted business areas. The focus is firmly on execution - ensuring change is understood, adopted, and sustained.

Key Responsibilities
Develop change management artefacts including stakeholder analysis, change strategy and plans, high-level and detailed impact assessments, communications, readiness assessments, schedules, and training plans
Execute agreed change activities to support successful adoption and embedding of change
Actively manage change-related risks, issues, and dependencies, including mitigation and resolution planning
Produce and deliver accurate, timely change status reporting for project teams, governance forums, and impacted stakeholders
Lead (where required) change-specific working groups, steering committees, and governance forums
Partner with internal and external stakeholders to create a collaborative environment that drives quality outcomes and smooth transition into BAU
Manage day-to-day change activities within cross-functional project teams, prioritising work based on capacity and capability
Establish and maintain an effective operating rhythm for change delivery
Assess change readiness, capacity, and capability, factoring in business cycles and customer/user impacts
Monitor and measure the effectiveness of change activities, iterating approach and execution as required
Coach and support change sponsors and change agents
About You
Demonstrated experience as a Senior Change Analyst (or equivalent) on complex transformation programs
Strong end-to-end experience developing and delivering change management artefacts
Experience working across Waterfall, Agile, and iterative delivery models
Confident engaging with senior stakeholders and navigating governance-heavy environments
Pragmatic, delivery-focused approach with the ability to adapt in fast-moving programs
Certification and hands-on experience with change methodologies such as ADKAR, Bridges, Lewin, and Kubler-Ross

A new role means a new way to win together. We’ve been proudly serving Australian communities since 1914 and at the heart of our continued success lies our 115,000 team members working across the country. If you’re looking for a career-defining opportunity, take the next step and explore another way your work can have impact and make a difference.

About the team

For a company as big as ours, the regulatory environment is complex and increasingly evolving. Our Compliance team are trusted advisors to the business, building programs and providing advice and support to help our teams comply with these evolving requirements.  At Coles, we are passionate about delivering quality products and exceptional service to our customers. As a leader in the retail industry, we are committed to maintaining the highest standards of compliance and regulatory adherence.

The Risk Systems Manager is responsible for leading the strategic and operational use of systems to support the effective management of Risk and Compliance across the organisation. This role bridges the gap between business needs and system capability, ensuring risk management frameworks, policies, and processes are supported by robust, fit-for-purpose technology solutions.


Experience required:



A sound working knowledge of risk and compliance management is essential.  Prior consulting experience is highly regarded, particularly in advising on system design and implementation in complex environments.




To define and execute the Coles Governance, Risk and Compliance system roadmap, including enablement of key governance, risk and compliance process. 




Proven experience managing or supporting systems in a Risk and/or Compliance environment.




Strong understanding of risk management and compliance frameworks, policies, and practices.




Experience in system implementation, configuration, and/or support.




Ability to manage multiple priorities and communicate effectively with technical and non-technical stakeholders.




Analytical and problem-solving skills with a focus on user experience and operational efficiency.




You will be responsible for:


Strategic systems management




Defining the Coles Governance, Risk and Compliance roadmap.




Optimisation of systems to support risk and compliance activities. 




Provide thought leadership on system capabilities, architecture, and improvements aligned to the Risk and Compliance strategy.

Lead system-related projects, including upgrades, enhancements, and integrations.



Operational management:


Collaborate with Risk and Compliance teams to translate business needs into system requirements.




Partner with IT and third-party vendors to implement and maintain effective system solutions.




Provide training and support to system users, ensuring consistent and effective use of tools.




Support delivery of Risk and Compliance reporting to the business and board.



System Governance & Compliance


Support the design and documentation of system processes, access controls, and audit trails.




Ensure data integrity, system security, and alignment with privacy and compliance obligations.




Develop and maintain governance documentation (e.g., procedures, user guides, change logs).



Continuous Improvement


Identify and implement opportunities to automate manual processes and improve system usability.




Stay up-to-date with industry trends and emerging technologies in risk systems and GRC platforms.




Qualifications:



Tertiary degree in Business, Information Systems, Risk Management, or a related field.




Familiarity with GRC platforms (e.g., RSA Archer, MetricStream, LogicManager, ServiceNow GRC, etc.) 




Project management and/or change management experience.

Exposure to risk reporting and data analytics tools.




Strategic thinker with a hands-on approach to problem-solving.




Excellent interpersonal and communication skills.




Adaptable and able to operate in a fast-paced, evolving environment.




Strong stakeholder engagement and relationship management capabilities.

What’s in it for you?

Flexible working options: We know that work is only one part of your life, so we actively encourage a positive work-life balance and provide hybrid working options to help you achieve it.
Office perks: Take advantage of our gym facility and fitness classes, free parking, BBQ area, mini-Coles supermarket, fooderie hub where you can sample new products before they hit the shelves, school holiday program and so much more when you come in.
Discounts: Eligible team members receive 5% discount all year round on your Supermarket and Liquor online and in-store purchases. We also offer additional periods of double discount (10%) at various times throughout the year. As well as hotdeals exclusive to team members that translate into additional savings.
Reward through recognition: Give and receive recognition, linked to our Coles values, through our digital recognition platform ‘mythanks’. You can accumulate points to redeem in the online shop for exciting gifts and electronic gift cards from an extensive range of retailers.
Opportunities for learning and development: No matter where you start within our diverse business, you’ll have experiences, exposure, and education to satisfy you. Discover and explore a variety of career development programs and job-specific training.
Paid parental leave: We understand how important your life outside work is and offer permanent team members paid parental leave to support you in balancing work and family.
Investment in your future: Our annual team member share plan offer allows eligible team members to make regular pre-tax salary sacrifice deductions to purchase Coles Group shares.

About the Role

Deliver internal audit engagements in accordance with icare’s Internal Audit Methodology, leveraging data analytics. Maintain positive relationships with key stakeholders across icare. Support the delivery of audits by executing risk and audit analytics. Support the definition and delivery of repeatable and insightful risk and audit analytics.

Benefits

A corporate wellbeing program with subsidised gym membership, free flu vaccinations and health check programs
17.5% annual leave loading
icare day – access to an extra day’s leave
Comprehensive learning and development support aligned to icare’s Core Capabilities.
Our People Awards - On-the-spot Recognition, Quarterly Values Awards & Our People Annual Awards
Access to our Employee Assistance Program

Duties

It’s an exciting time at icare where no two days are the same; as a Audit Lead - Technology you will:

Assist Internal Audit Leadership Team by leading and/or supporting the delivery the annual audit plan and non-audit related activities through use of data analytics and automation.
Perform data extraction, cleansing, and analysis across multiple sources to support audit objectives. 
Collaborate with audit teams and stakeholders to embed analytics into the audit lifecycle.
Stay current with emerging trends in Data Analytics and technology risk bringing forward practical application for audit.
Ensure quality outcomes are achieved in a timely manner, escalating all potential delays accordingly. ​
Support the delivery of audit reports that provide clarity on issues, root causes and associated risks with clearly articulated insights on the effectiveness of business processes, risk and control frameworks and / or strategy. ​
Engage and foster relationships with key stakeholders, including leadership to achieve effective outcomes, e.g. ensure deliverables are clearly articulated and potential issues are promptly identified and effectively addressed. ​
Review (as required) internal audit remediation actions committed by management. Undertake verification procedures to provide assurance that actions have been completed effectively. ​
Ensure deliverables and work products are factually accurate and convey insights which enhance the effectiveness and reputation of the internal audit function. ​
Contribute to the development of the annual risk-based Internal Audit Plan to ensure that assurance coverage remains relevant and sufficient relative to the risk profile of the organisation. ​
Maintain high standards of integrity and accountability. Facilitate the integration of risk management into day-to-day business activities and processes.​
Challenge the status quo to continuously improve processes both within the Internal Audit Unit and the areas being audited. ​
Maintain professional development, as required under the Global Internal Audit Standards (GIAS). 

Skills & Experience

Minimum 5 years experience in Audit Data Analytics including Data cleaning and preparation, Data visualisation tools, programming and reporting.
Well-developed understanding of audit procedures and standards.
Minimum 5 years experience in internal audit, and at least 3 years relevant experience in the financial services industry within the general insurance industry.
Demonstrated expertise in authoring conscious audit reports, which clearly articulate audit findings, their potential impact on business processes and associated risk and control environments.
Demonstrated experience in the adoption of technology or other operational level changes that have resulted in improving Internal Audit’s efficiency and ability to provide enhanced coverage.

 

Culture

We know our strength comes from the diversity of our people and would encourage people with different experiences and backgrounds to apply.   We are committed to our people’s development so the people of NSW can thrive.

We care for the people of NSW, building confidence and trust so our communities can thrive. We make the complex simple, so our schemes deliver better outcomes for people and communities. Whether a person is severely injured in the workplace or on our roads, icare supports their long-term care needs to improve quality of life, including helping people return to work.

Job Title: Senior Business Analyst - Data and Digital Solutions
Ad Text:
Who we are

TasPorts is a state-owned company responsible for ten Tasmanian ports and the Devonport Airport. We are a vertically integrated organisation providing a diverse range of port and marine operations and services around Tasmania. Our vision is to proudly connect people, products and solutions for the benefit of all Tasmanians.

With 99% of the State’s freight moving through our multi-port system, TasPorts facilitates vital trade to enable industry partners and communities while ensuring the highest environmental and safety standards.

The role

As we continue to modernise our operations and uplift our digital and data maturity, we’re seeking a Senior Business Analyst to play a key role in shaping the future of digital and data solutions across TasPorts.

Reporting into the IT Program Manager, the Senior Business Analyst will lead the analysis, discovery, and requirements definition that underpin our digital transformation initiatives. You’ll partner with operational, corporate, and technical stakeholders to translate business needs into actionable solution designs that support TasPorts’ strategic priorities and operational excellence.

This is a senior role ideal for someone who thrives in complex environments, enjoys engaging diverse stakeholder groups, and brings both analytical depth and strong communication capability.

Responsibilities 

Lead end-to-end business analysis across digital, data, and technology projects

Facilitate workshops, process mapping, and requirements gathering with stakeholders across ports, marine operations, corporate services, and asset management

Develop detailed business, functional, and technical requirements

Partner with project managers, solution architects, data specialists, and vendors to ensure solution alignment

Assess current-state processes and identify opportunities for optimisation, automation, and digital enhancement

Support business case development, feasibility assessments, and options analysis

Contribute to enterprise digital and data standards, ensuring solutions align with organisational strategy

Champion user experience, change readiness, and adoption throughout project delivery

This role is based in the TasPorts Hobart Corporate office.




About you

The key experience we are looking for includes: 

5+ years of demonstrated experience as a Business Analyst working on digital projects, products, or transformation initiatives.

Experience eliciting, documenting, and managing requirements throughout the project lifecycle.

Experience collaborating with multidisciplinary delivery teams.

Background supporting testing, defect triage, and validation of digital solutions against defined requirements.

Experience contributing to change readiness, user training, and adoption activities for digital solutions.

Excellent analytical and problem‑solving skills, with the ability to translate complex issues into clear, actionable insights.

What you will have

Essential

·          Relevant tertiary qualification (e.g. Bachelor of Business, IT, Data).

·          Formal training or certification in Business Analysis (e.g., IIBA ECBA, CCBA, CBAP, BPMN).

·          Current unrestricted Tasmanian drivers licence.

·          Ability to acquire and maintain a Maritime Security Identification Card (MSIC).

Desirable

·          Certification or training in Waterfall and Agile project delivery frameworks (e.g., PRINCE2, Scrum Master, Agile BA, SAFe) is an advantage. 

Why TasPorts?

Play a key role in digital uplift across a critical Tasmanian organisation.

Work on impactful, state-significant digital and data initiatives

Supportive, inclusive and safety-focused culture

Opportunities for professional learning and career development

Flexible work options and competitive remuneration.

Where to next?

TasPorts offers a supportive and flexible work environment, professional development opportunities and a range of attractive employee benefits. 

We are committed to building an inclusive, diverse workplace where the individual differences of our employees are considered value-adding. We encourage applications from suitably qualified persons, including Indigenous Australians, people of all ages and people with a disability.

Cover Letter

Current CV
